<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00064</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REPUBLIC ACT NO. <b>RA11058</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT STRENGTHENING COMPLIANCE WITH OCCUPATIONAL SAFETY AND HEALTH STANDARDS AND PROVIDING PENALTIES FOR VIOLATIONS THEREOF</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Strengthening Compliance With Occupational Safety And Health Standards And Providing Penalties For Violations Thereof</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to strengthen compliance of the occupational safety and health (OSH) standards by: 1) outlining the responsibilities of both the employers and workers; 2) mandating the creation of workplace OSH structure; 3) imposing administrative and criminal penalties in the form of fine and imprisonment for non-compliance thereof just like in Singapore and the USA; 4) imposing joint and solidary liability of employers, contractors and subcontractors for OSH compliance; and 5) provide for compensation and employment insurance benefits as well as payment of required penalties to the State Insurance Fund.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>NOGRALES, KARLO ALEXEI B., NOGRALES, JERICHO JONAS B., AGLIPAY-VILLAR, EMMELINE, DE JESUS, EMMI A., BROSAS, ARLENE D., REVILLA, STRIKE B., CASILAO, ARIEL &quot;KA AYIK&quot; B., LOPEZ, MANUEL LUIS T., CASTRO, FRANCE L., ELAGO, SARAH JANE I., TING, RANDOLPH S., VELOSO, VICENTE &quot;CHING&quot; S.E., COSALAN, RONALD M., BELMONTE, RICARDO &quot;RJ&quot; JR. T., BAG-AO, KAKA J., GO, MARK O., MENDING, MAKMOD JR. D., DELOSO-MONTALLA, CHERYL P., VILLARIN, TOM S., LAOGAN, DENNIS C., ONG, EDWIN, UNABIA, PETER &quot;SR. PEDRO&quot; M., TUPAS, RAUL &quot;BOBOY&quot; C., CHIPECO, JOAQUIN JR. M., BERTIZ, ANICETO &quot;JOHN&quot; III D., SANTOS-RECTO, VILMA, PAPANDAYAN, MAUYAG JR. &quot;JUN&quot; B., TAN, ANGELINA &quot;HELEN&quot; D.L. M.D., MARTINEZ, ERIC M., TAMBUNTING, GUS S., MACAPAGAL ARROYO, GLOR